    {
      "id": "4d00029f74e4d04c9fdbebed6b98590a9690fb1f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2013-12-18 21:03:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nThis is OK. I wish that the other callers of mdt_getattr_internal() were protected as well, since lu_object_attr() will assert on non-exiting objects.\n\nI think that the checks for exists and !remote are getting a little unwieldy, not to mention unwieldy. Defining a mdt_object_find() variant that builds in checks for exists and !remote would be a good start. Second it would be worthwhile to refine HABEO_CORPUS in to one or more target handler flags that check some useful combinations of: that the a body was really passed, that body had a valid FID, that the object was found and that it existed locally.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
